---
import Card from '../ui/Card.astro';
---

<section id="teams" class="teamlevels-section" aria-labelledby="teams-heading">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="section-intro fade-up">
      <h2 id="teams-heading">Things I've leveled up teams on</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="teams-grid">

      <Card eyebrow="Design systems" title="Filling the gap" class="fade-up">
        <p>
          The team didn't have a designer. I took a night course through Booz Allen,
          got comfortable in Figma, acquired team licenses, and introduced Storybook as a
          living component reference. One person filling a gap turned into a workflow
          the whole team depended on.
        </p>
      </Card>

      <Card eyebrow="Client engagement" title="Winning the room" class="fade-up">
        <p>
          Part of stakeholder review cycles from early wireframe through final demo. Built
          interactive prototypes polished enough that the work routinely beat competing
          proposals. Being in the room to present those decisions made a larger
          impact than any individual deliverable.
        </p>
      </Card>

      <Card eyebrow="Code quality" title="Reviewing the code" class="fade-up">
        <p>
          Shaped how a team gave and received feedback on PRs — smaller diffs, comments
          that taught rather than blocked, and a test coverage baseline that caught issues early. The habit changed before any tooling did, and it was the habit
          that stuck.
        </p>
      </Card>

    </div>

    <div class="teams-divider" role="separator" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="teams-result">
      <Card eyebrow="The result" title="Promoted to lead within a year" class="promoted-card fade-up">
        <p>
          Within twelve months of joining <strong>Booz Allen Hamilton</strong>, I was promoted to lead, received three
          internal awards, and was selected by the department to attend <strong>AWS re:Invent</strong> in Las Vegas.
          The promotion and the recognition were a direct response to the design system work
          and the client-facing demos. Evidence that the changes actually changed how the team operated.
        </p>
      </Card>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .teamlevels-section {
    padding-block: var(--space-16);
  }

  .section-intro {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-8);
  }

  /* Inline code chips */
  .teams-grid :global(code),
  :global(.promoted-card) :global(code) {
    font-family: ui-monospace, 'Cascadia Code', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 0.82em;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--tone-primary) 10%, var(--tone-surface-strong));
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--tone-primary) 80%, var(--tone-text));
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
  }

  .teams-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .teams-divider {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--tone-border);
    margin-block: var(--space-12);
    opacity: 0.4;
  }

  .teams-result {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  :global(.promoted-card) {
    max-width: 580px;
    width: 100%;
    padding: var(--space-8);
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  @media (max-width: 920px) {
    .teams-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 680px) {
    .teams-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    :global(.promoted-card) {
      padding: var(--space-6);
    }
  }
</style>
